15/04/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- During a meeting in Belgrade on Monday (14 April), representatives of the Serbian Interior Ministry and the BiH Ministry of Security agreed on the need to intensify bilateral co-operation in the fight against organised crime and corruption in the region. Serbian Deputy Interior Minister Nenad Milic said they also discussed co-operation in apprehending war crimes suspects.
In other news, Serbian police announced Monday that they had arrested Momcilo Mandic, a former deputy interior minister of BiH. A close associate of war crimes indictee Radovan Karadzic, Mandic was arrested in Belgrade at the weekend. In BiH, the Office of the High Representative welcomed the news. (OHR Sources - 15/04/03; NTV Hayat, PBS BiH, Tanjug, RTRS - 14/03/03)
